===Adjective===
'''ready''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''readier''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''readiest''')

# [[prepared]] for immediate action or use
#: '''ready''' money
# [[inclined]]; [[apt]] to happen
# [[liable]] at any moment
#: The seed is '''ready''' to sprout.
====Etymology====
*Old Saxon GERAEDE
*Dutch GEREED
*German GERADE
*Viking (G)REIÐR
*Goth GARAIÞS
mean etymologycally "ready to ride".

